Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the broiler to high or the #oven{} to 500 degrees.

> If you have a grill, heat it up to high! You can cook the skewers and pork chops there.

In a #small pot{}, bring @water{1%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil. Soak the @wooden skewers{4} in a #shallow dish{} filled with water. Halve, peel, and slice the @red onion{1}(halved and sliced) into ½-inch wedges. Core, seed, and cut the @red bell pepper{1}(cored and seeded) into 1-inch pieces. Halve the @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise) and slice into half moons. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Zest, then halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved).

== Quinoa ==

Cook the quinoa: Place the @quinoa{1/2%cup} and @veggie stock concentrate{1} into the boiling water, cover, and reduce to a low simmer for about ~{15%minutes}, until tender. Keep covered until the rest of the meal is ready.

== Veggie Skewers ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the lemon zest, half the garlic, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon}. Thread the bell pepper, onion, and zucchini onto the skewers, alternating between each. Place onto a #baking sheet{}. Drizzle the oil mixture over the veggies and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Broil for about ~{8%minutes}, turning halfway through cooking, until lightly caramelized.

> If you're short on time, you can broil the veggies un-skewered, too!

== Pork Chops ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the @boneless pork chops{12%ounce} on both sides with salt and pepper. Add them to the pan and cook for ~{4-5%minutes} per side, until golden brown and cooked to desired doneness. Set aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

== Oregano-Mint Pesto ==

Mince the @oregano{1/4%ounce}(minced) and @mint{1/4%ounce}(minced). In a small bowl, combine the oregano, mint, remaining lemon zest, a large drizzle of olive oil, a pinch of garlic (to taste) and a squeeze of lemon juice (to taste). Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Serve the roasted veggie skewers on a bed of quinoa with the pork chops alongside. Drizzle over top with the oregano-mint pesto and enjoy!